com.interpss.dist

Interface DistNetwork

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.hazelcast.nio.serialization.DataSerializable, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, IAdaptable, IMultiNet, INetBranchElement<DistBus,DistBranch>, INetBusElement<DistBus>, INetworkElement, NameTag, Network<DistBus,DistBranch>, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DistNetworkImpl

    public interface DistNetwork
extends Network<DistBus,DistBranch>
    A representation of the model object 'Dist Network'. Dist Network class for distribution analysis. There are two dimensions for variations: 1) Multiple SC Points: 2) Muitiple Load Points: Nameplate Point:

    The following features are supported:

    • Positive Seq Data Only
    • Sc Std
    • Load Schedule Data
    • Sc Point Net Data
    • Fault Net
    See Also:
    DistPackage.getDistNetwork()

      • createAcscNetData

        void createAcscNetData()
                throws InterpssException
        Always use the first SC Point to create the AcscNet. Before create the network data, call (AcscNetwork)getFaultNet().setToEmpty(). At this point, we do not want to remove faults in the FaultNet.
        Throws:
        InterpssException

      • updateAcscNetData

        void updateAcscNetData(int scPointIndex)
        update the AcscNet data for the specfied SC point. Only the bus objects are updated. Sc point index is 0 based.
